📊 Poverty Level Analysis in Central Java 2020
Project Description:
This project analyzes poverty levels across regencies and cities in Central Java in 2020 using official data from Statistics Indonesia (BPS).
The analysis aims to identify regions with the highest and lowest poverty rates, compare poverty conditions across regions, and provide insights into socioeconomic disparities within Central Java.
The findings are presented through statistical summaries, rankings, and visualizations to support a better understanding of regional poverty patterns.

Project Objectives:
Analyze poverty levels across regencies and cities in Central Java in 2020.
Compare poverty rates among regions.
Identify areas with the highest and lowest poverty rates.
Visualize poverty data through charts and rankings.
Develop data analysis and interpretation skills using Microsoft Excel.

